<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently, Http_Client only allows the 8 HTTP/1.1 compliant request methods. However, several protocols based on HTTP (such as HTTPMail used by Outlook to connect to Hotmail and DAV used by Subversion) require additional request methods.</p>

<p>Additionally, the RFC specifically allows servers and clients to extend the common request methods and use different, non-RFC ones.</p>

<p>Currently I don't see any reason not to allow the user to send HTTP requests using arbitrary methods.</p>

